# Load the default devShell from the flake located in src/.
# nix-direnv caches the environment so re-entering the directory is instant.
use flake "./src"

# Install prek Git hooks if this repository opts into prek (prek.toml present).
# WHY: direnv fires on every directory entry; delegating hook installation here
# removes the need for a persistent zsh chpwd hook and keeps hook setup
# tied to the devShell lifecycle rather than the global shell session.
# prek install is idempotent; it is a no-op when hooks are already in place.
if command -v prek > /dev/null 2>&1 && [ -f prek.toml ]; then
  prek install
fi
